    "four_reasons": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"apotecha-reasons\"><h2 class=\"apotecha-reasons__heading\">4 Reasons<br>Why Women Are Switching To Rice Protein</h2><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__content\"><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__image\"><img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1008/2261/4403/files/Apotecha_shampoo_USP_s.jpg?v=1776074712\" alt=\"Apotecha shampoo bar\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"681\" height=\"681\"></div><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__list\"><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__item\"><span class=\"apotecha-reasons__num\">1</span><h3>Volumne</h3><p>Rice protein is rich in amino acids like cysteine and lysine, which help add body and fullness to fine, limp hair.</p></div><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__item\"><span class=\"apotecha-reasons__num\">2</span><h3>Strength</h3><p>The amino acids in rice protein help build healthy keratin, the protein that's responsible for helping reinforce the hair's cortex.</p></div><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__item\"><span class=\"apotecha-reasons__num\">3</span><h3>Shine</h3><p>The lipids in rice protein help fill rough spots in the hair cuticle, resulting in a smooth, healthy looking shine.</p></div><div class=\"apotecha-reasons__item\"><span class=\"apotecha-reasons__num\">4</span><h3>Balance</h3><p>Rice protein doesn't strip natural oils. Its milder amino acids clean without disrupting the scalp's natural pH balance.</p></div></div></div></div>",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "section_width": "page-width",
        "padding-block-start": 80,
        "padding-block-end": 80
      }
